For the good price, location, and services you get with this hotel, I think it's a small price to pay to learn to shower a slightly different way.	The price is quite reasonable and you feel like you are in Paris as opposed to staying in a standard Hilton.I wouldn't stay again even though I was happy as I think there is better value to be had.	It's not expensive, nor is it super cheap...so you get an *excellent* location, comfy beds, but subpar linens, microscopic rooms (even the superior rooms are a tight fit for two people with lots of luggage), polite service, but not many amenities (no kitchen/roomservice, spotty wifi, cheap soap).